column5: Managed to find a buddy of mine for a company today. Started at 7:30am and both of us came home with our limit. Had to sort through a lot of dinks though...was surprised to not see too many fish been caught by others and we must have passed by hundreds of fishermen...it was like mini-Toronto on the ice today. We were lucky as we had fish under our holes for most of the day.  Over 6"-7" of ice where we were.  Time now to get ready for the big boys next weekend - lakers and whities. Hope we have enough ice in their grounds by next weekend.  One shot from today as it was nice day but very cold with the NW wind for most of the day.    Cheers, Ice Fisherman
Well done.  That looks like a nice white bucket,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,of fish.
Glad to hear you guys got into some good numbers today !!!!....cheers
Emil  You should of called!!!  I probably passed right by you!!!!  I am getting my fill of cleaning Perch also!!!!!  But we need a couple more COLD nights.    Wont be Long   You have a PM  Rick
looks good I think I might get out for a while tomorrow
Great report and pic icefisherman  Looks like you guys put a beating on them... WTG  Thanks for sharing Leechman
Terry  Head out Early!!!  Parking is at a Premium!!!  Rick
OH Yea!!  Travelling is about perfect 8" Ice, 2" Snow, 0 Cracks!!!  The Biggest Crack you cross is right at Shore!!!  Have Fun  Rick
Today is a great day. We fished on Cooks bay. Some spots were almost non-stop.  Two of us landed about 200+. Average size are good.
Fine work, Emil. I know we are going to get out for the white type o fish shortly.  Good post.
